{
  "act_id": "act_symmetry_time",
  "title": "Symmetry & the Landing Clock",
  "viz_panel": "svg",
  "beats": [
    {
      "say": "Look at this arc. The left half and right half are perfect mirror images — whatever the ball does climbing up, it undoes on the way back down. Same shape, same time, just reversed.",
      "card": null,
      "viz_actions": [
        {
          "method": "reflectArcSymmetry",
          "params": {},
          "offset": "0"
        }
      ],
      "inline_viz": null,
      "duration": null
    },
    {
      "say": "That symmetry gives us a clean question: when does the ball return to ground level? In other words, when does $y(t) = 0$?",
      "card": null,
      "viz_actions": [
        {
          "method": "showEquation",
          "params": {
            "step": "yOfT",
            "position": "top"
          },
          "offset": "0"
        },
        {
          "method": "showEquation",
          "params": {
            "step": "setZero",
            "position": "top"
          },
          "offset": "+1.2"
        }
      ],
      "inline_viz": null,
      "duration": null
    },
    {
      "say": "Set $y(t) = 10\\sqrt{2}\\,t - 4.9t^2 = 0$ and factor out $t$. You get $t\\,(10\\sqrt{2} - 4.9t) = 0$ — two solutions appear immediately.",
      "card": {
        "type": "derivation",
        "title": "Solving for Flight Time",
        "steps": [
          {
            "latex": "y(t) = 10\\sqrt{2}\\,t - 4.9t^2 = 0"
          },
          {
            "latex": "t\\,(10\\sqrt{2} - 4.9t) = 0",
            "highlight": true
          },
          {
            "latex": "t = 0 \\quad \\text{or} \\quad t = \\frac{10\\sqrt{2}}{4.9}"
          }
        ]
      },
      "viz_actions": [
        {
          "method": "showEquation",
          "params": {
            "step": "factored",
            "position": "top"
          },
          "offset": "0"
        }
      ],
      "inline_viz": null,
      "duration": null
    },
    {
      "say": "$t = 0$ is just the launch — not useful. The second solution is what we're after: $t = \\dfrac{10\\sqrt{2}}{4.9} \\approx 2.89$ seconds. That's our landing clock.",
      "card": {
        "type": "latex",
        "content": "T_{\\text{flight}} = \\frac{10\\sqrt{2}}{4.9} \\approx 2.89 \\text{ s}",
        "highlight": true
      },
      "viz_actions": [
        {
          "method": "highlightSolution",
          "params": {
            "solution": "nonzero"
          },
          "offset": "0"
        }
      ],
      "inline_viz": true,
      "duration": null
    }
  ]
}